Two alleged illegal miners were killed and two others arrested in a stand-off with a private mining security company in Boksburg on Friday. It is alleged the shooting between a group of alleged illegal miners started following a conflict over territorial boundaries. Two bystanders were injured after being caught in the crossfire. Ekurhuleni Metropolitan Police Department spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Kelebogile Thepa said two alleged illegal miners were killed, while two others were arrested. Two pistols were confiscated by the police. Thepa added the scene was under control. Meanwhile on Thursday, the case against 87 suspected illegal miners arrested after a deadly shootout with police in Orkney in October was transferred from the Orkney Magistrate's Court to the Regional Court in Stilfontein, the North West. The accused were arrested in Orkney following a shootout with law enforcement officers.